node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'COMMUNITY GUIDELINES ON SOCIAL MEDIA Our Team is devoted to providing a respectful, inclusive and safe space for all Formula One fans on our social media channels.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'THE POWER Social media has an incredible power to bring people together and unite them, no matter the team and driver you support. It's a place where everyone can share their passion and make their voice heard.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'OUR SOCIAL MEDIA POLICY When interacting online, we ask that you follow our Community Guidelines and echo the values we stand for; to show respect, inclusivity kindness when engaging online. and There is no place for discrimination, hate or eene of any kind on social media.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'EQUALITY AND INCLUSIVITY We are committed to fighting all forms of discrimination and ensuring our online community represents the values that we stand for.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TAKING ACTION If any interactions we see on our channels do not meet our Community Guidelines, we will take appropriate action. Those actions can range from removing the posts and comments, blocking and reporting accounts, to escalating incidents to the relevant authorities or social media platforms if we feel it is appropriate or required.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YOUR POWER You, our fans and followers, also hold the power. The power to call out unacceptable behaviour, report comments or users who don't meet our community guidelines, and flag issues with us. This all plays a big part in making our community a safer and more inclusive place.'.

Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on September 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'FAMILIARISE YOURSELF make If you want to our community a more respectful, inclusive and safe space, we recommend you review and familiarise yourself with our Community Guidelines: MERCEDESAMGF1.COM/#COMMUNITY'.
